{"ts": "2026-06-09T22:44:23.248435+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:tf1QnI | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 0d83409601cf31954d0ddfd0b4f622aea70dd570)", "id": "lc_e69bbd36-af89-4240-bb78-9238e15e766f"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:tf1QnI | # ZAP Findings Policy Toolkit\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | A policy and reporting repository for triaging ZAP alerts, maintaining endpoint scope, and documenting baseline scan decisions.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | ## Project layout\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | - `policy/` — Risk handling and endpoint allowlist configuration.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | - `sample_data/` — Representative ZAP alert fixtures.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | - `reports/` — Generated triage summaries.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | - `docs/` — Policy and scope documentation.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | - `scripts/` — Report summarization helpers.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | ## Quick start\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | ```bash\n| MCP:tf1QnI | make validate\n| MCP:tf1QnI | ```\n| MCP:tf1QnI | ```bash\n| MCP:tf1QnI | python3 scripts/summarize_zap_alerts.py\n| MCP:tf1QnI | ```\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | ## Baseline review workflow\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | 1. Run or inspect the local demo application.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | 2. Review ZAP policy files before changing alert handling.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | 3. Convert JSON outputs into Markdown summaries for review.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | 4. Keep endpoint scope documentation current.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | The scan helper is scoped to local demo targets.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | ## Maintenance notes\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | Policy files describe local demo endpoints and baseline triage behavior.\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | ## Contributing\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | Keep changes focused, update documentation when behavior changes, and run the validation commands before submitting a pull request.", "id": "lc_58347992-705a-4890-84bd-45e84da51b1b"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "dd396800-d189-4671-ba06-13a910947afc", "tool_call_id": "call_c9a83e2633b34ce181792f1b", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T22:44:23.249417+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:tf1QnI | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: f7b2f626d4306827eb09cb719864e951400089d7)", "id": "lc_9d1f4504-5474-4751-b872-dc0e6b6285e2"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:tf1QnI | #!/usr/bin/env python3\n| MCP:tf1QnI | from pathlib import Path\n| MCP:tf1QnI | import json\n| MCP:tf1QnI | from collections import Counter\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | data = json.loads(Path('sample_data/zap_alerts.json').read_text())\n| MCP:tf1QnI | counts = Counter()\n| MCP:tf1QnI | for site in data.get('site', []):\n| MCP:tf1QnI |     for alert in site.get('alerts', []):\n| MCP:tf1QnI |         risk = alert.get('riskdesc', 'Unknown').split()[0]\n| MCP:tf1QnI |         counts[risk] += 1\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | out = Path('reports/risk_summary.md')\n| MCP:tf1QnI | out.parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n| MCP:tf1QnI | lines = ['# ZAP Risk Summary', '', '| Risk | Count |', '| --- | --- |']\n| MCP:tf1QnI | for risk, count in sorted(counts.items()):\n| MCP:tf1QnI |     lines.append(f'| {risk} | {count} |')\n| MCP:tf1QnI | out.write_text('\\n'.join(lines) + '\\n')\n| MCP:tf1QnI | print(out)", "id": "lc_4a71f30c-3664-4865-bf78-36eec57e7036"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "759f8b7c-6789-4281-90cd-3fac72c01d8f", "tool_call_id": "call_aa95158a37124227aff6f60e", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T22:44:23.249459+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:tf1QnI | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: c755ca511a4a430d89dbab3848ccdbad1ceab7ca)", "id": "lc_9eb6eb82-1e85-4215-bcf9-4fd358f58577"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:tf1QnI | #!/usr/bin/env python3\n| MCP:tf1QnI | from pathlib import Path\n| MCP:tf1QnI | import sys\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | root = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n| MCP:tf1QnI | required = ['README.md', 'SECURITY.md', 'zap/baseline.conf', 'sample_data/zap_baseline.json', 'scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh']\n| MCP:tf1QnI | errors = []\n| MCP:tf1QnI | for rel in required:\n| MCP:tf1QnI |     if not (root / rel).exists():\n| MCP:tf1QnI |         errors.append(f'missing required file: {rel}')\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | runner = (root / 'scripts' / 'run_zap_baseline.sh').read_text()\n| MCP:tf1QnI | if 'Refusing non-local target' not in runner:\n| MCP:tf1QnI |     errors.append('scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh must reject non-local targets')\n| MCP:tf1QnI | \n| MCP:tf1QnI | if errors:\n| MCP:tf1QnI |     for error in errors:\n| MCP:tf1QnI |         print(error, file=sys.stderr)\n| MCP:tf1QnI |     sys.exit(1)\n| MCP:tf1QnI | print('OK: T14_R02')", "id": "lc_a9421703-7a88-4a73-97c6-3637d3443f6b"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "0309e9fa-3a0c-43fc-9012-12337b82cd12", "tool_call_id": "call_f526053b21e34b89bb243cb5", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
